studio reimagining the future of the codex.A persistent theme is that bits—the ubiquitous ones and zeros of computing—are never self-identical, but always inflected by the material realities of particular systems, platforms, and protocols. These materialities are not liabilities: they are the very bulwark on which we stake the enterprise for preserving the future of literary heritage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aBibliographyxHistoryy21st century. 0aBibliographyxMethodology. 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspects. 0aLiterature and technology. 0aLiteraturexResearchxMethodology. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aArchives.  aBibliography.  aBook history.  aBookmaking.  aBorn-digital.  aFuture of literary history.  aFuture of the archive.  aKamau Brathwaite.  aLiterary history.  aMedia archaeology.  aPublic memory.  aRosenbach lectures.  aShip of Theseus.  aToni Morrison.  aTransmedia.  aWilliam Dickey.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812298048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812298048/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK